message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Assumed-not-Earned: Verification Efficiency under Bounded Risk"
abstract: >-
  A cross-domain study of when verification should stop, given a cost of checking
  and a risk of being wrong. A non-refutation overhead boundary has a provable risk
  bound under a correct prior and a silent, unbounded failure under misspecification;
  the same law governs whether added model structure is earned. Spans number theory,
  cosmology, control, statistics, and LLM evaluation under a pre-registered,
  fabrication-averse protocol.
